A: You are using the same dataSnapshot.getChildren().iterator() in every iteration of your loop. This means that you are always getting the first child from the list.
Instead, you should use the iterator of the loop variable itself. Here is the corrected code:
names=new ArrayList<>();
rootRef.addValueEventListener(new ValueEventListener() {
    @Override
    public void onDataChange(DataSnapshot dataSnapshot) {
        for (Iterator<DataSnapshot> it = dataSnapshot.getChildren().iterator(); it.hasNext(); ) {
            i = i + 1;
            names.add(it.next().getValue(String.class));
        }
        Toast.makeText(signup.this,""+names,Toast.LENGTH_LONG).show();
    }

    @Override
    public void onCancelled(DatabaseError databaseError) {
        // Handle the error
    }
});

This way, you are getting the value of each child in the loop.

